==English==
===Etymology===
Coined in translation of [[w:François Rabelais|Rabelais]]' works, derived from the obsolete French [[metagrabouliser]], to [[mystify]].

===Noun===
'''metagrobolism''' ([[mass noun]])

# [[concealment|Concealment]], [[mystification]], [[obfuscation]]. ''[[facetious|Facetious]].''
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*'''1653''': [A]ll the autonomatic '''metagrobolism''' of the Romish Church, when tottering and emblustricated with the gibble-gabble gibberish of this odious error and heresy, is homocentrically poised. &mdash; François Rabelais, ''Gargantua and Pantagruel''

